author: Inside Edition
description: "Stranger Things" star Millie Bobby Brown stunned in a black corset at Thursday night's GQ Men of the Year bash in Hollywood. Sydney Sweeney also showed up to the 90s-themed party in a choker necklace and smokey eye makeup. Supermodel Hailey Bieber also took the red carpet by storm in a Gucci gown. Olivia Rodrigo brought out the sparkles in an elegant shoulder-strap number from Tom Ford. Meanwhile, LA Dodgers slugger Shohei Ohtani celebrated his fourth MVP win.
title: Stunning Looks From This Year's GQ 'Men Of The Year' Red Carpet

author: Inside Edition
description: Alex Murdaugh, a prominent lawyer, was convicted of murdering his wife and son. The family's devoted housekeeper spoke with Inside Edition. Blanca Turrubiate-Simpson tells Eva Pilgrim that in the 14 years she worked for Maggie and Alex Murdaugh, there was never a hint of the horror to come. Maggie and son Paul were found shot to death at the family estate in South Carolina. Turrubiate-Simpson has written a book, "Within the House of Murdaugh: Amid a Unique Friendship - Blanca and Maggie."
title: Murdaugh Family House Keeper Blanca Turrubiate-Simpson Speaks Out

author: Inside Edition
description: A Jonas Brothers concert goer's attention drifted to his phone, looking at a person's resume that came his way. Another fan sitting nearby took notice and recorded a video. Jenn Wilson posted the video to TikTok with the caption, "Scott Kelly your resume was being reviewed at a Jonas Brother concert tonight. Good luck." The video went viral with 51 million views. Scott Kelly, and the man who was looking at the resume, Brandon Bieron, spoke with Inside Edition.
title: His Resume Went Viral At a Jonas Brother's Concert, He Speaks Out

author: Inside Edition
description: Vice President JD Vance joked on Fox News that President Donald Trump gets zero sleep. CNN's Kaitlyn Collins says travelling on Air Force One is exhausting. The president claims he can get by on just four hours of sleep a night, but his lack of sleep may be catching up with him. Last week, Trump appeared to doze off in the Oval Office in the middle of a press conference as Dr. Oz was talking about getting a good night's sleep. Inside Edition spoke with sleep expert Dr. Sanam Hafeez.
title: How Much Sleep Does President Donald Trump Get?

author: Inside Edition
description: Five-year-old Carson Combs was waiting for the school bus when police say his grandmother ran him over in the family's driveway, killing him. Police say the boy's grandmother was pulling out of the driveway in a large SUV on her way to work when she realized she ran over something and stopped. To everyone's horror, it was Carson. He died instantly. Police say the grandmother was under the influence of alcohol and depressants. Kristen Anders was booked for vehicular homicide.
title: 5-Year-Old Killed After His Grandmother Runs Him Over

author: Inside Edition
description: This author got an egg-throwing heckler at his book launch event in Spain, which turned out to be just the latest episode of a real-life telenovela that's been going on for years. The author, Luis Rubiales, used to be the head of the country's soccer federation. Then in 2023, he kissed a member of the Women's World Cup winning team during the medal ceremony. His book reportedly details his account of his professional downfall. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Man Shows Up To Nephew's Book Launch To Throw Eggs At Him: Reports

author: Inside Edition
description: This suspect proved difficult to catch. Then again, it had an unfair advantage: four legs instead of two. Police in Albuquerque, New Mexico, closed down part of a highway to catch this wild pig that wandered into traffic. It had these cops chasing it by car and by foot. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Cops Chase Wild Pig Running Around Highway In Albuquerque
